social_posts.post_text: Our sweet boy is 3 months! His personality is coming out. He is so smiley and is starting to find his voice with lots of babbling, screaming with delight, and every so often we get a hint of a giggle. I don’t know how he’s growing so fast.
Ewan’s 1st Christmas 🎄❤️
One for the books 🫶🏼 #2022

My beautiful boy is 4 months 🥹

This past month he met the rest of his cousins & was the loudest of the bunch 😅 He has been super cuddly lately and is curious about everything. I need time to slow down.
Go Niners!
Mom & Dad’s big night out at @smithcenterlv! We had a blast seeing @moulinrougebway! It’s one of my all-time favorite movies and seeing it come to life on stage was so magical ✨

Celebrating year 2 as a family of 3. You changed my whole world 💞 I love you the most.

You giggle, you fake cough for attention, you love being outside, you love sitting at the table with us, and you love snuggling us like a little koala. I can feel your love when your face lights up when you see us. You are just wonderful 💞

I can’t believe our chatty, cuddly, curious, playful guy is already 9 months! His top teeth popped through this weekend for the occasion! Time doesn’t feel real. I hope my memory of him at this age never fades 🤍
40 weeks in —> 40 weeks out ❤️
Busy day for Ewan! He visited me at @fox5vegas this morning and made his impromptu on-air debut!
Just when I thought I couldn’t love you more, I watched you become the best daddy. We love you! Happy Father’s Day!

One of my favorite Bay Area events of the year is coming back! I am proud to once again be the MC for the @leaninlatinas Take Charge conference! A day to learn, network, and empower! Head to @leaninlatinas to learn more and register! #LatinasTakeCharge

My pretty Juniper 🩷

I can’t believe 11 months have flown by! Ewan has recently started to crawl and move around A LOT… it was so hard to get good pics! 
Our sweet, funny, and curious boy— you fill us with so much love. I’ve been emotional this week, you would think he’s headed off to college.
Family time means more now than ever ❤️ Ewan had such a fun time splashing around with his cousin Maddox and celebrating his cousin Sofia’s 13th birthday!

I blinked. I can’t believe our sweet boy is already ONE. It’s been a whirlwind. It’s been wonderful. It’s been life changing in every way. If I had to pick any year to live over and over again, it would definitely be this one. You are loved beyond measure ❤️

😮‍💨 what an experience! 
Darren Aronofsky’s Postcard From Earth took us to the most beautiful places in the world. A ride-like experience in which you can see, smell, and feel the awe-inspiring vastness of our home. It was both a love letter to our beautiful planet and a dire warning for its inhabitants. “We thought these ruins were relics of the past, but they were portals to the future.” 
My takeaway: we are all too self-centered to take serious climate action. “A billion spokes that all think they’re the center of the wheel.” 
I 10/10 recommend experiencing this at @spherevegas for yourself! 
Tip: if you park at the Venetian, the pedestrian bridge you need to take is connected to the Venetian convention center
We tried to get Ewan to play with the pumpkins but he really digs the gravestones 🪦
Welcome to Jurassic Park 🦖🦕
Not a great game but misery loves (good) company. Go pokes!
We were so busy cooking and hosting our family for Thanksgiving we forgot to take a picture! But here we are prepping for the madness. I’m so thankful for my boys ❤️
First time seeing the lights at Ethel M 🌵🎄I think we have a new holiday tradition!

Amazing morning (as always) hosting the @oppvillagelv Las Vegas Great Santa Run! Thank you to the thousands of Santas who came out to support OV’s incredible work! This is my favorite event of the year! 🎅🏻🏃‍♂️
We are so excited to add another little one to the family! Baby #2 coming June of 2024!
Our first Christmas staying at home with our little fam ❤️🎄 it’s not Ewan’s first Christmas, but it feels like it with him being a little older! He and Juno both loved the wrapping paper 😂

We have many reasons to celebrate 2023. Among the highlights:
-Lots of quality time with family & friends
-We bought (and did lots of work to) our first home
-Acquired 4 desert tortoises 
-Celebrated Ewan’s first birthday 
-Found out we’re expecting baby #2! 

We look forward to all the new things coming in 2024!

🩵 Boy mom
